1️⃣ VERBAL ABILITY – ERROR DETECTION (GRAMMAR BASICS)

This topic is very important for written tests + interviews.

🔹 A. WHAT IS ERROR DETECTION?

👉 You are given a sentence
👉 You must find the incorrect part

🔹 B. COMMON ERROR TYPES

1️⃣ Subject–Verb Agreement
2️⃣ Tense errors
3️⃣ Articles (a, an, the)
4️⃣ Prepositions
5️⃣ Basic grammar mistakes

🔹 C. SUBJECT–VERB AGREEMENT (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Singular subject → singular verb
👉 Plural subject → plural verb

🔹 Example 1

❌ He go to school
✅ He goes to school

🔹 Example 2

❌ They goes to college
✅ They go to college

🔹 D. TENSE ERROR
🔹 Example 3

❌ I am knowing the answer
✅ I know the answer

🔹 Example 4

❌ She go yesterday
✅ She went yesterday

🔹 E. ARTICLES
🔹 Example 5

❌ He is a honest man
✅ He is an honest man

🔹 F. PREPOSITION ERROR
🔹 Example 6

❌ She is married with him
✅ She is married to him

📝 PRACTICE QUESTIONS

Find the error:

He do his work regularly
She have completed her task
I am having a car
He is a MBA graduate
They was playing cricket
